Mineral Resources Minister Gwede Mantashe will lead a South African government delegation to the yearly Africa Down Under exhibition, which is being held in Perth, Australia, from August 29 to 31. Mantashe will also address delegates at the event and host the South African Mining Investment Seminar under the theme ‘Ensuring a competitive, sustainable and transformed South African mining’. This seminar is expected to reaffirm South Africa’s commitment to growing and sustaining the mining industry and confirm the country as a preferred investment destination.